00:18:09.453 --> 00:18:17.683
fires, and fewer bad things that happen on Friday 13 than on a normal day, presumably because

00:18:17.913 --> 00:18:24.053
people are careful, or they just avoid activities that could be considered dangerous in any way.

00:18:24.903 --> 00:18:28.673
So, if you are listening to this episode on Friday the 13th, I

00:18:28.673 --> 00:18:32.523
hope you’re having a marvelous day, full of good luck and joy.

00:18:33.503 --> 00:18:39.013
And if you’re listening to this episode and Friday the 13th has been and gone without

00:18:39.023 --> 00:18:44.543
you noticing any bad luck, congratulations, you’ve survived, and at least you now know a

00:18:44.553 --> 00:18:49.583
little bit more about where this superstition, and superstitions in general, come from.

